    "culture_note": "Twi uses the Latin alphabet minus c, j, q, v, x, z — plus two special vowels: ɛ (the ‘e’ in ‘bed’) and ɔ (the ‘aw’ in ‘law’). Master these two and Twi spelling suddenly makes sense. The digraphs ky, gy, hy soften to ‘ch’, ‘j’, ‘sh’."
